<br>
&nbsp;
<h1 style="color: #9ac864;display: block;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: 30px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 100%;letter-spacing: normal;margin-top: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 10px;margin-left: 0;text-align: left;">Sencha Official</h1>

<p><a href="http://www.sencha.com/blog/using-the-new-app-watch-command-in-sencha-cmd-4" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Using the New App Watch Command in Sencha Cmd 4</a></p>

<p>Don Griffin describes an excellent feature of Sencha Cmd 4 - App Watch. This feature enables us to quickly see changes we make to our apps without having to manually run rebuild commands.</p>

<hr>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h1 style="color: #9ac864;display: block;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: 30px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 100%;letter-spacing: normal;margin-top: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 10px;margin-left: 0;text-align: left;">Sponsor</h1>

