<hr>&nbsp;
<h1 style="color: #9ac864;display: block;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: 30px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 100%;letter-spacing: normal;margin-top: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 10px;margin-left: 0;text-align: left;">JavaScript</h1>

<p><a href="http://gu.illau.me/posts/dont-optimise-javascript/" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Don&#39;t optimise JavaScript</a></p>

<p>A very insightful article about the approach one should take when trying to optimise web applications and the likelihood that JavaScript isn&#39;t always on the top of the list of possible performance culprits.</p>

<p><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2013/12/21/mozillas-asm-js-gets-another-step-closer-to-native-performance/" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Mozilla&rsquo;s Asm.js Gets Another Step Closer To Native Performance</a></p>

<p>asm.js took a step closer to reaching true native speeds. The latest update brings the code to a performance level of 1.5x or better than that of native code.</p>

<p><a href="http://ariya.ofilabs.com/2012/12/complexity-analysis-of-javascript-code.html" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Complexity Analysis of JavaScript Code</a></p>

<p>Measuring code complexity is a useful tool to understanding your code and how it could be improved. Phil Booth has created an interesting library to measure your JavaScript&#39;s code complexity which is described in this article.</p>

<h1 style="color: #9ac864;display: block;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: 30px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 100%;letter-spacing: normal;margin-top: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 10px;margin-left: 0;text-align: left;">HTML5</h1>

<p><a href="http://flippinawesome.org/2013/12/23/parallax-ui-for-phonegap-and-mobile-web-apps/" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Parallax UI for PhoneGap and Mobile Web Apps</a></p>

<p>This article shows us how to create a parallax UI similar to the effect used on the iOS 7 home screen.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.sitepoint.com/use-html5-vibration-api" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">How to Use the HTML5 Vibration API</a></p>

<p>One of the newest browser APIs on the scene (and possibly one with the most potential for annoying users...) is the Vibration API. This article describes how it is used and where we can use it right now.</p>

<p><a href="http://phonegap.com/blog/2013/12/13/phonegap-release/" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">PhoneGap 3.3.0 Released</a></p>

<p>PhoneGap&#39;s relentless release cycle is continued with the release of version 3.3.0. This update introduces official support for Android KitKat alongside a number of other bug fixes and general improvements.</p>

<h1 style="color: #9ac864;display: block;font-family: Tahoma;font-size: 30px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 100%;letter-spacing: normal;margin-top: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 10px;margin-left: 0;text-align: left;">CSS</h1>

<p><a href="http://rupl.github.io/unfold/" style="color: #0088cc;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">Unfolding the Box Model: Exploring CSS 3D Transforms</a></p>

<p>Chris Ruppel introduces a very informative presentation about 3D transforms with CSS.</p>
